# Referencia: Diagramas Mermaid (Regra #2)

## Quando Usar

| Tipo de Mudanca | Diagrama | Obrigatorio? |
|----------------|----------|-------------|
| Novo endpoint | sequenceDiagram | Sim |
| Mudanca de schema | erDiagram | Sim |
| Nova integracao | flowchart | Sim |
| Bug fix | — | Nao |
| Config/refactoring | — | Nao |
| CRUD basico | — | Nao |

## Exemplos

### Sequence Diagram (novo endpoint)
```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    Frontend->>Backend: POST /api/v1/resource
    Backend->>Database: INSERT INTO resource
    Database-->>Backend: OK
    Backend-->>Frontend: 201 Created
```

### ER Diagram (mudanca de schema)
```mermaid
erDiagram
    RESOURCE {
        uuid id PK
        string name
        timestamp created_at
    }
```

### Flowchart (nova integracao)
```mermaid
flowchart LR
    A[Service A] --> B[Service B]
    B --> C[Database]
```
{{else}}
# Reference: Mermaid Diagrams (Rule #2)

## When to Use

| Change Type | Diagram | Required? |
|------------|---------|-----------|
| New endpoint | sequenceDiagram | Yes |
| Schema change | erDiagram | Yes |
| New integration | flowchart | Yes |
| Bug fix | — | No |
| Config/refactoring | — | No |
| Basic CRUD | — | No |

